race.description: Freeman Wauchope Timber Celebrates 100 Years Hcp
race.comment: This looks like a ripping race for a BM70. ZUNNA (11) was favourite for a similar race last week but failed to gain a start as an emergency. Seven days later, she finds a winnable race. She's won two of her four starts and has plenty of upside. Drawn well to get the right run for Opperman. She can win this. DELIGHTFUL SHECKY (2) is back from Melbourne and, while he will go around at double figures, he is good enough to win this and can finish somewhere in the money. PEARL ADIOS (1) is another classy horse on his day, as was the case last start when he won over 1400m. He is a track and distance winner who can go close here. CLARENCE (5) needs the favours in the run but he has enough ability to run top three, while FROM THE BLOCK (6) can go forward with the 3kg claim and will be hard to run down.
